Let us have a simple visualization of the rejection sampling technique.

<<>>=
h_scaled <- function(x) p(x) / (M * q(x))
@

<<>>=
df %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = x, y = u, shape = result)) +
  geom_point() +
  scale_shape_manual(values = c("accepted" = 16,
                                "rejected" = 1)) +
  stat_function(fun = h_scaled, linewidth = 1.25, inherit.aes = FALSE) +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank())
@

\smallpencil \hspace{0.1cm} The $(x, u)$ pairs that fall under the curve are accepted and rest are rejected.

